org.firewaterframework.mappers
Class MethodMapper

java.lang.Object
  org.firewaterframework.mappers.Mapper
      org.firewaterframework.mappers.MethodMapper

public class MethodMapper
extends Mapper

Responsible for parsing out the REST Method (GET, PUT, POST, etc.) and dispatching to delegate Mappers based on this information. This class is also responsible for implementing a cacheing scheme based on OSCache. The reason for putting the cacheing here is that the REST Method implies a cacheing action as follows:

  • GET,HEAD,OPTIONS - fetch from the cache if possible - otherwise delegate and cache response
  • PUT,POST,DELETE - flush the cache and cache groups for this URL

Note that each mapper can specify the cacheGroups for resources. This allows Mappers that are related to flush each other on PUT,POST, or DELETE operations to this resource.

getCacheGroups

public java.lang.String[] getCacheGroups()

setCacheGroups

public void setCacheGroups(java.lang.String[] cacheGroups)
Setting cacheGroups for a Mapper allows several Mappers to in effect share caches. When a cache is flushed (during a POST,PUT, or DELETE), all cacheGroups associated with this Mapper will also be flushed.

Parameters:
cacheGroups - a collection of cacheGroup names
See Also:
Cache

setEntryRefreshPolicy

public void setEntryRefreshPolicy(com.opensymphony.oscache.base.EntryRefreshPolicy entryRefreshPolicy)
Allows for creating a cache flushing policy based on a time period. This allows a time based cache flushing policy for those times where external processes may modify the underlying resources without the REST layer knowing about it.

Parameters:
entryRefreshPolicy - a specification of a time for periodic flushing of this Mapper's cache
